                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9085: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-29T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 29, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 29—4:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>353. My 347, July 24, 1 p.m. During my conversation with Count Ciano this
                    afternoon I asked for information with regard to the Far Eastern situation. He
                    said that a telegram had just been received from Peiping to the effect that all
                    of the Italian residents in Peiping, some 35 in number, had been assembled in
                    the Italian Embassy. He was confident that there would be no declaration of war
                    on the part of the Chinese Government for obvious reasons. He had already
                    instructed the Italian Ambassadors in Tokyo and in Nanking to urge the
                    respective Governments to adopt peaceful measures and at the same time he had
                    offered the services of the Italian Government “in mediation” if that would be
                    of help in the present situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
